ed within the new GS IT ISEC organization to further reduce the risk to an acceptable level.\n\nMapped to Global ERM: R_2015_GS_IT_033','400','2018-10-10 11:27:00','2018-10-10 11:27:00'),(2820,64,'E','-','400','2018-10-10 11:27:00','2018-10-10 11:27:00'),(2821,64,'F','2.8','400','2018-10-10 11:27:00','2018-10-10 11:27:00'),(2822,64,'G','Information Technology','400','2018-10-10 11:27:00','2018-10-10 11:27:00'),(2823,64,'H','N/A','400','2018-10-10 11:27:00','2018-10-10 11:27:00'),(2824,64,'I','N','400','2018-10-10 11:27:00','2018-10-10 11:27:00'),(2825,64,'J','8','400','2018-10-10 11:27:00','2018-10-10 11:27:00'),(2826,64,'K','4','400','2018-10-10 11:27:00','2018-10-10 11:27:00'),(2827,64,'L','20','400','2018-10-10 11:27:00','2018-10-10 11:27:00'),(2828,64,'M','High','400','2018-10-10 11:27:00','2018-10-10 11:27:00'),(2829,64,'N','8','400','2018-10-10 11:27:00','2018-10-10 11:27:00'),(2830,64,'O','4','400','2018-10-10 11:27:00','2018-10-10 11:27:00'),(2831,64,'P','20','400','2018-10-10 11:27:00','2018-10-10 11:27:00'),(2832,64,'Q','High','400','2018-10-10 11:27:00','2018-10-10 11:27:00'),(2833,64,'R','Business Objectives','400','2018-10-10 11:27:00','2018-10-10 11:27:00'),(2834,64,'S','','400','2018-10-10 11:27:00','2018-10-10 11:27:00'),(2835,64,'T','-','400','2018-10-10 11:27:00','2018-10-10 11:27:00'),(2836,64,'U','','400','2018-10-10 11:27:00','2018-10-10 11:27:00'),(2837,64,'V','','400','2018-10-10 11:27:00','2018-10-10 11:27:00'),(2838,64,'W','-','400','2018-10-10 11:27:00','2018-10-10 11:27:00'),(2839,64,'X','Roth Francois-Xavier','400','2018-10-10 11:27:00','2018-10-10 11:27:00'),(2840,64,'Y','-','400','2018-10-10 11:27:00','2018-10-10 11:27:00'),(2841,64,'Z','Yi Feng','400','2018-10-10 11:27:00','2018-10-10 11:27:00'),(2842,64,'AA','Reduce','400','2018-10-10 11:27:00','2018-10-10 11:27:00'),(2843,64,'AB','Medium','400','2018-10-10 11:27:00','2018-10-10 11:27:00'),(2844,64,'AC','Q3 2020','400','2018-10-10 11:27:00','2018-10-10 11:27:00'),(2845,64,'AD','- Protection Concepts: The criticality of Information and IT assets will be re-assessed jointly with the business starting in FY16. Focus in FY17 is continue the development and implementation of protection concepts for those assets . \n\n- Cyber Detection & Monitoring: Cyber Defense Centers (CDC) in North America successfully started. Enhancement of detection capabilities is ongoing. CDC Europe  go live in Q1/FY16. CDC Latin Americas in Q2/FY16 while go-live for CDC Asia is planned for Q4/FY16.\n\n- NextGen Active Directory: a revised, secure Active Directory is defined, providing enhanced monitoring capabilities. Rollout started in Q1/FY16. \n\n- Incident Remediation: The incident remediation process is revised to ensure timely response and limit the impact of incidents. Training and rollout will be completed by end of Q4/FY16 (in cooperation with GM SEC and CT RTC).\n\n- Global Malware Protection: An enhanced Global Malware Protection is effective for GAIN countries. Non-GAIN countries are planned to be included by end Q4/FY16.\n\n- Housekeeping Activities: continue the remediation of critical access management vulnerabilities on mailboxes and file shares. \n\n- Awareness: The annual Web Based Training will be rolled out by Q3/FY16, adressing ~300.000 Siemens users on the topic of cyber attacks by social engineering. In addition, ISEC participation in IT Roadshows and IT Masterclass to raise awareness of employees. \n\n- Data Leakage Protection ','400','2018-10-10 11:27:00','2018-10-10 11:27:00'),(2846,64,'AE','70','400','2018-10-10 11:27:00','2018-10-10 11:27:00'),(2847,64,'AF','ó','400','2018-10-10 11:27:00','2018-10-10 11:27:00'),(2848,64,'AG','-','400','2018-10-10 11:27:00','2018-10-10 11:27:00'),(2849,64,'AH','RIC: \n\nFY18, Q1:Progress:\nDetailed measures have been updated for FY2018 which include topics: Asset Protection, Cyber Detection&Monitoring, service scope and focus topics of ISEC China team, Vulnerability Management, Global & Local Training, Data Leakage