peration','400','2018-10-10 11:27:02','2018-10-10 11:27:02'),(3352,77,'D','On 1/6/2017 the Cyber Security Law of the PRC has come into force. Siemens China is defined as “Network Operator” according to our internal evaluation. The law defines requirements for Network Operator in the aspects of Personal Information Protection, Cross-border Data Transfer, Multi-Level Protection System and Security Incident Handling. Even though Siemens already set-up a \"Internal Operation Project\" to mitigate the risk, there might still be potential risks as followed:\n- ambiguous and broad definition of the law may lead to different interpretation of the requirements.\n- the application & systems used in Siemens China are incompletely/incorretly coverred in the scope of the project. It might lead to insufficient mitigation actions.\n- Wrongly position Siemens as network operator instead of Critical Information Infrastructure Operator (CIIO), which lead to the requirements mandatory for CIIO neglected.','400','2018-10-10 11:27:02','2018-10-10 11:27:02'),(3353,77,'E','-','400','2018-10-10 11:27:02','2018-10-10 11:27:02'),(3354,77,'F','4.3','400','2018-10-10 11:27:02','2018-10-10 11:27:02'),(3355,77,'G','Legal and Regulatory','400','2018-10-10 11:27:02','2018-10-10 11:27:02'),(3356,77,'H','N/A','400','2018-10-10 11:27:02','2018-10-10 11:27:02'),(3357,77,'I','N','400','2018-10-10 11:27:02','2018-10-10 11:27:02'),(3358,77,'J','2','400','2018-10-10 11:27:02','2018-10-10 11:27:02'),(3359,77,'K','9','400','2018-10-10 11:27:02','2018-10-10 11:27:02'),(3360,77,'L','13','400','2018-10-10 11:27:02','2018-10-10 11:27:02'),(3361,77,'M','Medium','400','2018-10-10 11:27:02','2018-10-10 11:27:02'),(3362,77,'N','2','400','2018-10-10 11:27:02','2018-10-10 11:27:02'),(3363,77,'O','9','400','2018-10-10 11:27:02','2018-10-10 11:27:02'),(3364,77,'P','13','400','2018-10-10 11:27:02','2018-10-10 11:27:02'),(3365,77,'Q','Medium','400','2018-10-10 11:27:02','2018-10-10 11:27:02'),(3366,77,'R','Regulatory Bod